{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "One specific method of stress-testing such models is via contrast sets [8].",
    "A contrast set C(x) is essentially a sample of points around a data point x, that is close to the local ground truth decision boundary.",
    "Samples in C(x) may have same or different ground truth label as x.",
    "In practice, C(x) can be a set of samples that are 'close' to x, i.e., have minimal edit distance from x, yet be 'challenging' for a trained model to classify.",
    "In the original contrast sets work [8], the authors advocate for an evaluation paradigm where dataset authors themselves create and release such contrast sets for model evaluation."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "One specific method of stress-testing such models is via contrast sets [8].",
    "In the original contrast sets work [8], the authors advocate for an evaluation paradigm where dataset authors themselves create and release such contrast sets for model evaluation."
  ]
